    "narrative": "The Austin Waves head into today\u2019s slate with **Kyle Tucker** (76.67) and **Jackson Merrill** (70.91) anchoring the offensive output. **Kyle Tucker** is the clear priority start; despite a pending lineup confirmation, he benefits from a favorable matchup against Colin Rea (xERA 4.36) and a significant park boost with wind blowing out. Similarly, **Jackson Merrill** draws a high score thanks to a robust platoon advantage against Gallen. While **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (67.40) and **Miguel Vargas** (60.61) also clear the 60-point \"Strong\" threshold, the team must remain cautious regarding the high-end talent on the mound today; **Drake Baldwin**, **Gunnar Henderson**, and **Dominic Smith** all face an elite arm in Zack Wheeler, whose 2.73 xERA severely dampens their projected efficiency scores.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench was undoubtedly **Marcell Ozuna** (47.28). While he remains a core component of our roster, he fell just short of the efficiency baseline required to crack the starting lineup over players like **Dominic Smith** or **Heliot Ramos**, primarily due to a negative adjustment against a difficult opposing starter. The optimizer prioritized the specific platoon advantages of the other starters, leaving **Marcell Ozuna** as the primary pivot should any last-minute lineup changes occur. We are also monitoring the status of **Drake Baldwin**, **Jacob Wilson**, **Andy Pages**, **Kyle Tucker**, and **Dominic Smith**, as their \"Lineup Pending\" status introduces late-scratch risk. With **Gunnar Henderson** and **Heliot Ramos** facing challenging left-handed pitchers in Crochet and P\u00e9rez, maintaining our focus on high-efficiency, high-floor matchups remains the priority for today\u2019s rotation.",
